**What**: The missed optimization involves a pattern of `xor` between two `select` instructions (or their logical equivalents) where one is a logical OR and the other is a logical AND, both controlled by the same boolean condition. Specifically, the pattern:

```llvm
%o = select i1 %y, i1 true, i1 %c    ; -> equivalent to %c | %y
%a = select i1 %c, i1 %x, i1 false   ; -> equivalent to %c & %x
%r = xor i1 %o, %a
